    "However, for the Traffic Dataset, TXtreme shows comparable results to other methods (RMSE and MAE of 0.02).",
    "The limited improvement is because of low variablility inTable 4 Comparison of various models using RMSE and MAE for test data Dataset Evaluation matrix FFNN DeepAR N-BEATS WaveNet Trans-former TXtreme Solar RMSE 7.21 7.22 6.62 7.31 7.23 6.10 MAE 3.28 3.28 3.52 3.55 3.28 3.01 Traffic RMSE 0.02 0.02 0.02 0.03 0.03 0.02 MAE 0.01 0.01 0.02 0.01 0.02 0.01 Electricity RMSE 519.06 477.99 510.91 489.91 514.68 451.22 MAE 354.39 329.75 350.37 286.56 398.80 244.23 Web Traffic RMSE 2719.65 2981.91 2820.62 2719.37 3815.38 2614.13 MAE 2025.23 2272.58 2051.30 2025.50 3100.32 1988.13the data.",
    "The traffic dataset has a low RMSE and MAE across all models, which is due to fewer extreme values and that the data follows a more consistent pattern, which minimizes the advantage of TXtreme.",
    "If the dataset does not contain significant extreme events, the added complexity of TXtreme may not provide a meaningful advantage over simpler models like FFNN or DeepAR that already perform well with stable, non-extreme data.",
